ass=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₁}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">H</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u₃}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₁, u₁}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v₃, u₃}</a> <span class=\"fn\">H</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor\">Functor</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <span class=\"fn\">H</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">W</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/MorphismProperty/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.MorphismProperty\">MorphismProperty</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given `F : C ⥤ H`, `W : MorphismProperty C` and `X : C`, we say that `F` has a\npointwise left derived functor at `X` if `F` has a right Kan extension\nat `L.obj X` for any localization functor `L : C ⥤ D` for `W`. In the\ndefinition, this is stated for `L := W.Q`, see `hasPointwiseLeftDerivedFunctorAt_iff`\nfor the more general equivalence. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Derived/PointwiseLeftDerived.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.HasPointwiseLeftDerivedFunctorAt","kind":"class","line":41,"name":"CategoryTheory.Functor.HasPointwiseLeftDerivedFunctorAt","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Derived/PointwiseLeftDerived.lean#L41-L49"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Functor.Derived.LeftDerived","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Functor.KanExtension.Pointwise","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Localization.StructuredArrow"],"instances":[{"className":"CategoryTheory.Functor.HasLeftDerivedFunctor","name":"CategoryTheory.Functor.hasLeftDerivedFunctor_of_hasPointwiseLeftDerivedFunctor","typeNames":[]},{"className":"CategoryTheory.Functor.IsLeftDerivedFunctor","name":"CategoryTheory.Functor.instIsLeftDerivedFunctorLiftHomFac","typeNames":["CategoryTheory.Localization.lift","CategoryTheory.Iso.hom"]}],"name":"Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Functor.Derived.PointwiseLeftDerived"}